720384f-b.text:
(1)
327 and 325 Henry Street, at and adioining its junction with Grand Street. The 3-story frame building (No. 327) at the corner also bears No. 527 Grand Street and forms the apex of the afore-mentioned junction. No. 325, the 1-story frame house is at the rear of No. 525 Grand Street; a 3-story frame house. Contiguous to it is a 1-story frame addition used as a garage which bears no number. IIt is at the rear of 523 Grand Street, a frame building with a rear wall made of brick. Also shown (extreme right) is No. 530 Grand Street, north
side, between Columbia and Cannon Streets.
June 6, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
A portion of the same, at a later date, showing a more inclusive view
of No. 325.
March 23, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
